        <p>In <xref ref = "activity-limits-graphically1"/> we got an approximation to the limit of the function as <m>x</m> tends to 2.  Now let us say you are given the same plot as in <xref ref = "activity-limits-graphically1"/>, but also given a table of numerical values (<xref ref="table-limit-numerical2"/>) for the function. Given this new information which of the choices below best describes the limit of the function as <m>x</m> tends to 2?  </p>
    <ol marker="A">
            <li><p> There is not enough information because we do not know the value of the function at <m>x = 2</m></p></li>
            <li><p> Can be approximated to be 1 because the data in the table and the graph show that from the left and the right the function approaches 1 as <m>x</m> goes to 2 </p></li>
            <li><p> Can be approximated to be 1 because the values appear to approach 1 and the graph appears to approach 1, but we should zoom in on the graph to be sure </p></li>
            <li><p> Cannot be approximated because the function might not exist at <m>x = 2</m>.</p></li>
